#: 21337012-0-1630
msgctxt "21337012-0-1630"
msgid ""
"Once, a maiden prayed to Leki for guidance.\n"
"\n"
"\"\"Blessed saint of the spirit-sword,\"\" said the maiden, \"\"send me a "
"sign! Do I follow my mother's order to marry, or do I resist?\"\"\n"
"\n"
"Her intended husband was a much older man, who was said to have killed his "
"former wives by means so cleverly concealed, nothing could be proven. And "
"yet, his prestige amongst the nearby towns was so high, no one dared refuse "
"to negotiate a bride-price with him.\n"
"\n"
"The maiden, whose name was Zarrineh, knelt at the shrine for a full night "
"and a day before returning to her village. She'd heard no answer, and as the "
"time for her wedding drew near, she despaired.\n"
"\n"
"On the night before her wedding, Zarrineh dreamt she was a fisherwoman, "
"casting her net into the sea and drawing it in. Each time she drew the net "
"into the boat, she saw a flash of silver that was not a fish's scale. On the "
"third draw, she examined the silver flash and realized it was a small "
"dagger, with a carved handle of ironwood.\n"
"\n"
"When she awoke, Zarrineh found such a blade beneath her pillows, though she "
"knew it had not been there before.\n"
"\n"
"And so, Zarrineh's husband found himself unable to dispose of his new bride "
"with the same ease as his previous wives. For when she showed him the blade "
"and told of her prayers to Leki, he realized Zarrineh was protected by the "
"saint.\n"
"\n"
"They lived together many years, and he treated Zarrineh well, always mindful "
"of the blessed dagger in her keeping."
msgstr ""

