"\n"
"* * *\n"
"\n"
"Once, in the long-ago time, the people were content to live in the forests "
"and hunt on the plains. They fed and ate and mated, and all was good—but it "
"was also simple. The people saw the two-legs, sometimes, and knew they could "
"do so much more if they could reach the skies. \n"
"\n"
"Then, one day, a wise old monk came to the people. She said her name was "
"Azurah. She had been watching the people, she said, and had decided to give "
"them a gift. A special kind of candy, she said."
