"<<1>> saw it first. A panther, with eyes bright as the moons shining "
"overhead. We'd set the decoy earlier in the day, and with an arrow loosed it "
"past the beast.\n"
"\n"
"Somehow it guessed our treachery! That old monster turned and glared at the "
"blind we'd thought hidden so well in the underbrush. It snarled, and like a "
"black wind did rush us with all its speed.\n"
"\n"
"<<1>> let fly an arrow. Swift as lightning did it plunge into the beast's "
"eye, yet still it charged on! When it reached my spear, its bulk lifted me "
"from the ground. Were my grip not sure, I'd have sprawled into the trees "
"above, so powerful were its death throes.\n"
"\n"
